        "text": " - ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "After this thing",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " [calculated though it was to make a deep impression and to furnish a solemn warning] ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Jeroboam turned not from his evil way.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " \"Some hand was found that durst repair the altar God had rent\" (Matthew Henry). According to Josephus, the old prophet now explained away the miracles of the prophet of Judah, alleging that the altar had fallen because it was new and the king's hand had become powerless from fatigue (Ant., 8:09, § 1)], ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "but made again",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " [Heb. \"",
        "children": []
      },
      {
