      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "filled his hand",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". In the consecration of Aaron and his sons, and possibly of their successors also, the portions of the victim which were usually burned upon the altar, together with the right shoulder or leg, which was the priest's portion, and three cakes of unleavened Bread, were put into the hands of the candidates for the priesthood, and waved before the Lord before they were offered on the altar (",
