        "text": "Leviticus 8:25-28",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). To \"fill the hand\" consequently Became a synonym for consecration] ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "him",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " [It would almost appear, from the extreme readiness with which Jeroboam ordained his priests, that few candidates offered themselves for the office. In one respect, however, he exacted more from the candidate than did the law. For whereas the latter required \"one bullock and ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "two",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " rams\" (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Exodus 29:1",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", etc.), he demanded one Bullock and ",
